The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Monday, April 05, 2004 				 Addicts kill girl for earrings
																								Behrampore, April 4: Alleged drug addicts forced four-year-old Sabina Khatun to part with her gold earrings and then murdered her last night. 																								Sabina was last seen playing with friends near her Sammatinagar home last evening. When she did not return, everyone went looking but could not find her. A missing complaint was lodged. We recovered her body from an abandoned house on the outskirts of the village this morning, a police officer said. Two drug addicts lured her away with the promise of chocolates. 																								Three people were arrested. Murshidabad superintendent of police Gyanwant Singh said: They have confessed. They killed her when she started screaming. Sabinas friends described the culprits to the police. 																								Singh said the duo asked her if the earrings were made of gold. She nodded. They were sold to a local jeweller for Rs 405.
